      • getDefaultInstance

        public static com.google.protobuf.Message getDefaultInstance(com.google.protobuf.Descriptors.Descriptor message)
        Returns a default instance for the given message descriptor. First tries to get it from a concrete class representing the message. If that fails, falls back to use DynamicMessage, which works, but is significant slower on parsing and such.

      • getEnum

        public static com.google.protobuf.ProtocolMessageEnum getEnum(com.google.protobuf.Descriptors.EnumValueDescriptor enumValueDescriptor)
        Returns a Enum for the given enum value descriptor. It tries to get it from a concrete class representing the Enum. Returns null if cannot find the Enum.
